HEADWORD: Goosery
<hw>Goos"er*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Gooseries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A place for
keeping geese.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The characteristics or actions of a goose;
silliness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The finical <qex>goosery</qex> of your neat sermon actor.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>goose skin</ent>⟦br⟧
